    303          /*******************************************************************************
    304          * Function Name  : I2C_FlagClear
    305          * Description    : Clears the I2C Flag passed as a parameter
    306          * Input          : - I2Cx: specifies the I2C to clear its flags, it can be:
    307          *                     I2C0, I2C1 
    308          *                  - Flag: the flag to be read, it can be:
    309          *                     I2C_ADD10, I2C_EVF, I2C_BERR, I2C_ARLO, I2C_STOPF
    310          *                     I2C_AF, I2C_ENDAD, I2C_SB, I2C_ADSL, I2C_BTF, I2C_TRA
    311          *                     I2C_M_SL, I2C_GCAL
